description.narrative: Children, parents, caregivers and communities have knowledge of at least three key protective behaviours for children, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2019, leading decision makers will have increased knowledge about child-rights issues and children and caregivers have positive behaviours around infant and maternal care, child protection, participation and social protection.

title.narrative: Children, parents, caregivers and communities have knowledge of at least three key protective behaviours for children

description.narrative: In 2019, parents and caregivers have their knowledge of nutrition, health, hygiene and sanitation and protective practices increased. Over 59,3 thousand caregivers (58% women, 42% men) of children 0-59 months in drought affected areas had their knowledge in nutrition and hygiene areas increased. In areas affected by Polio outbreaks, 11,5 million people had their knowledge increased on Polio risks and preventive measures, which contributed to the Polio vaccination of 5 million children U5. The work of 19 thousand social mobilizers in 16 of 18 Provinces of Angola were crucial to the achievement of the results. | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/01/2020
